### Message shown when jEdit is first run
first-time.title=Welcome to jEdit
first-time.message=Thank you for installing jEdit!\n\
	\n\
	While jEdit is very useful on its own, it can be made even more\n\
	powerful by installing "plugins". Plugins are modules of code\n\
	that add features to jEdit.\n\
	\n\
	Would you like to see a list of available plugins and download\n\
	any that interest you? (This requires an Internet connection.)\n\
	\n\
	Note that you can install plugins at any other time by selecting\n\
	Plugins->Plugin Manager->Install New Plugins.

new-version.title=New Version Installed
new-version.message=You have just upgraded from jEdit version {0} to {1}.\n\
	Because this new version might have introduced plugin-related\n\
	changes, it is recommended that you update all your plugins to\n\
	their latest versions to avoid any problems.\n\
	\n\
	Would you like to update your plugins now? (This requires an\n\
	Internet connection.)\n\
	\n\
	Note that you can update plugins at any other time by selecting\n\
	Plugins->Plugin Manager->Update Plugins.

